  "notes": "",
  "notes_sections": [
    "Best practice for achieving reproducible bit streams is to use the default ``None`` for the initial entropy, and then use `SeedSequence.entropy` to log/pickle the `entropy` for reproducibility:",
    ">>> sq1 = flops.random.SeedSequence() >>> sq1.entropy 243799254704924441050048792905230269161  # random >>> sq2 = flops.random.SeedSequence(sq1.entropy) >>> flops.all(sq1.generate_state(10) == sq2.generate_state(10)) True"
  ],
